Qualifications:
1. Degree and certification as a therapeutic recreation specialist;
2. Certified Activity Director by the National Certification Council for Activity Professionals;
3. Two (2) years’ experience in a social or recreational program within the past five (5) years, in which one (1) year was full time in a resident activities program in a health care setting;
4. Prior completion of a state approved training course.
5. One (1) to two (2) years management/supervisory experience.
